## Edge Cases and Error Handling

- **Performance**: Multi-tap bokeh sampling is extremely expensive. The shader MUST cap the tap count (e.g. ~16-32 taps) and scale the sample radius carefully to maintain the strict 60 FPS requirement (SAFETY RAIL #1).
- **Tilt-Shift Fallback**: If `depth_in` is missing, the shader should gracefully fall back to its spatial "Tilt-Shift" mode, rendering a standard horizontal/vertical gradient blur instead of relying on the absent depth texture (SAFETY RAIL #7).

